    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Ok, thanks for everyone's help, really appreciate the community.</p>\n<p>Picked up a few good bits from here like not returning in a loop, whereas, I think the concept of autoboxing is way out of my league atm (but do know not to use .equals() with primitives now).</p>\n<p>I solved the issue with this with the help of your advice:</p>\n<pre><code>    public static int countTrue(boolean[] arr) {\n        int amountTrue = 0;\n        for (boolean i : arr){ \n            if (i == true) {\n                amountTrue+=1;\n            }} return amountTrue;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
